[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scottish soldier Shaun Cole died in Miami 'accidentally'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The death of a soldier from Edinburgh has been deemed ''accidental'' by police in North America.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Officers had been investigating the possibility Shaun Cole, 22, had been a victim of crime when his body was found on a Florida pavement in March.
The Royal Scots Borderer had been on holiday at the Ultra Music festival in Miami with two friends when he died.
Pte Cole had recently returned from serving in Sierra Leone, where he was helping with the fight against Ebola.
Police in America had earlier said the former Tynecastle High School pupil had suffered a blunt force trauma to the head. It has now judged this to have been from an accident.
